    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "The project aims at contributing to the consolidation and restoration of selected damaged monuments and temples of the Hanumandhoka (Kathmandu) Durbar Square of the Kathmandu Valley World Heritage Site. The project will provide continuous monitoring of the damaged monuments, assess further risk and provide immediate protection. Selected monuments at risk of collapse will be consolidated and restored. The project will contribute to establishing the basis for long-term reconstruction and rehabilitation of the Nepali cultural heritage. The project will also contribute to the restoration of local economies by creating employment and on-the-job training opportunities."
      },
